{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":353250,"duration_api_ms":334394,"num_turns":33,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"05c8f9bd-3eba-413c-a15a-c903d91ac1fb","total_cost_usd":1.7325875000000004,"usage":{"input_tokens":24,"cache_creation_input_tokens":92414,"cache_read_input_tokens":1534960,"output_tokens":15496,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":92414,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":24,"outputTokens":15496,"cacheReadInputTokens":1534960,"cacheCreationInputTokens":92414,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.7325875000000004,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"In `unique_terminal_replay_match` (fs.rs ~line 2837), the `debug_assert!` was replaced with a silent `return None`. The issue spec requires 'runtime checks that return errors in both debug and release builds.' While callers do produce an error when `None` is returned, the specific contract violation reason (run_id supplied without started_at) is lost, making debugging harder. Add a `tracing::error!` or `tracing::warn!` log before returning `None` so the contract violation is diagnosable in production logs, or change the return type to `Result<Option<usize>>` and return an explicit error.","rationale":"The spec explicitly asked for error returns, not silent fallthrough. In production, if this contract is violated due to a caller bug, the operator sees only a generic 'no matching task run' error with no indication that the real cause is a missing started_at on a named completion. A single tracing line would preserve the diagnostic intent of the original debug_assert while satisfying the 'all build modes' requirement."},{"body":"`TaskRunEntry::merge_attempt_entries` (model.rs ~line 320) uses the same manual field-by-field pattern that was identified as drift-prone for journal details (issue 1), but has no compile-time or test-time guard against omitted fields. Add a round-trip coverage test analogous to `journal_merge_fills_all_optional_fields`: construct a primary with all optional fields None and a secondary with all fields populated, merge, serialize both the merged entry and the secondary, and assert the optional-field subset matches. This would catch a forgotten merge line when a new optional field is added to `TaskRunEntry`.","rationale":"The issue explicitly aimed to prevent 'silently discarded fields during repair.' The journal detail structs now have this protection, but `TaskRunEntry::merge_attempt_entries` — which performs the same fill-absent-fields pattern for lineage rows — does not. A new optional field added to TaskRunEntry without updating merge_attempt_entries would silently drop data during duplicate-row repair, the exact same class of bug the issue set out to prevent."}],"summary":"The implementation correctly addresses all three issues from the spec. Issue 1 (duplicate journal structs): the fs.rs duplicates are eliminated; model.rs structs are shared with Serialize+Deserialize, deny_unknown_fields removed, serde(default) on optional fields, and explicit field-by-field merge replaces the generic json_fill_none helper. Round-trip and merge-coverage tests guard against drift. Issue 2 (runless-to-named completion): the debug_assert is replaced with a runtime check; started_at is required for disambiguation in both open-entry and terminal-replay paths; the pre-filter by started_at correctly excludes unrelated completed attempts. Issue 3 (plan_hash auto-population): new entries auto-populate from snapshot with provenance tracking via snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation; existing open rows use safe_plan_hash_backfill with provenance verification; terminal replays correctly skip auto-population; snapshot read failures log warnings and degrade gracefully. All 683 tests pass, clippy clean, fmt clean. Two minor amendments proposed: (1) the contract violation in unique_terminal_replay_match should log rather than silently return None, and (2) TaskRunEntry::merge_attempt_entries lacks the drift-guard test that was added for journal details."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"effb66b6-0905-40e8-b70d-9771709a47c0"}
